thats exactly the problem.  the game may be evolving, but its not doing it properly.<br>
<br>
the stronger the player base is, the faster they clear every mob in existance, longer we spend bored waiting for repops, the more verant has to rebalance, and the more verant breaks things in the process.<br>
<br>
if the levels are raised without rebalancing, the old expansions are trash.  if they are raised WITH rebalancing, verant will have to spend time doing the rebalancing.  if they did that, they would spend less time fixing bugs already in the game to make more. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usanistan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanistan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/13/02 7:57:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1262.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: level cap raised</span><hr size=1> I think I would quit if they didn't raise the level cap =P<br>
